  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Released\u00a005/09/2017 11:21 CT (16:21 UTC)</p><h2 id=\"id-1.12.7-SalesSummarybyStaffReport\">Sales\u00a0Summary by Staff Report</h2><p>Two fixes are submitted in this update.</p><ul><li><p>The report now applies the\u00a0catalog item filter accordingly</p></li><li><p>The sales % column is fixed (i.e. no longer displaying zeros)</p></li></ul><h2 id=\"id-1.12.7-Deviceview,ticketlink\">Device view, ticket link</h2><p>The ticket link on the device view is fixed.</p><h2 id=\"id-1.12.7-InventoryRefurbPermission\">Inventory Refurb Permission</h2><p>The permission rule for creating refurb tickets from inventory items has been separated out from the base inventory edit permission; the permission\u00a0can now be configured separately from inventory editing (e.g. allowing refurb creation without also allowing inventory editing).</p><p><em>Permissions customization is only available on the Enterprise Plan</em></p><h2 id=\"id-1.12.7-RepairDeviceNotes\">Repair Device Notes</h2><p>The spacing for line/paragraph breaks was &quot;doubled&quot;\u00a0when the new text markup tool was introduced in RepairQ 1.12.5. This issue has been resolved, and the spacing is now what it was before the 1.12.5 update.</p>",
